That's right, these exoskeletons do not fly but for that you could use

00:01:11.190 --> 00:01:16.470
Yves Rossy suit, he developed a jet pack shaped like a wing with multiple engines

00:01:16.470 --> 00:01:20.570
similar to those used in aircrafts worldwide. This jet pack allows him to fly long distances,

00:01:20.570 --> 00:01:27.390
for example Yves Rossy tried to cross from Morocco to Spain in his suit...

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:29.030
and he missed...just by 5 km.

00:01:29.030 --> 00:01:33.910
So, if you combine a military exoskeleton with this jet pack shaped like a wing

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:37.100
you could be Iron man? and fight against aliens and robots?

00:01:37.100 --> 00:01:41.960
Well about that, TALOS exoskeleton is still in development, mainly because it's batteries

00:01:41.960 --> 00:01:47.560
are really heavy, and they lose charge very quickly. And the Yves Rossy suit, only works

00:01:47.560 --> 00:01:52.610
when the flight begins from a certain altitude. In other words, he needs to get on a plane or a helicopter,

00:01:52.610 --> 00:01:55.450
and then jump to start it's flight.

00:01:55.450 --> 00:01:59.350
So, if you wanted to be Iron man nowadays, you would have to jump from a plane

00:01:59.350 --> 00:02:04.580
to start flying, and carry a lot of batteries to fight.

00:02:04.580 --> 00:02:09.280
However, Iron man, solves this battery problem with a miniature nuclear reactor

00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:13.030
that allows him to provide almost infinite energy to his suit.

00:02:13.030 --> 00:02:18.069
Unfortunately nowadays all nuclear reactors are huge and they obviously

00:02:18.069 --> 00:02:19.829
do not provide infinite energy

00:02:19.829 --> 00:02:24.280
Well...in regard to this topic, a good candidate for providing energy to Iron Man's armor

00:02:24.280 --> 00:02:29.249
is nuclear fusion. Nuclear fusion happens when you take Hidrogen atoms called

00:02:29.249 --> 00:02:35.249
Deuterium and Tritium and you expose them to pressures and temperatures as high as the ones

00:02:35.249 --> 00:02:39.379
found in our Sun. This makes these hydrogen atoms to fuse together, resulting in Helium

00:02:39.379 --> 00:02:42.049
and an immense quantity of energy

00:02:42.049 --> 00:02:47.659
However, it is worth pointing out that nuclear fusion,  is not the same as nuclear fission, which is

00:02:47.659 --> 00:02:52.650
the nuclear power used nowadays by almost every nuclear reactor in the world. So in nuclear fusion

00:02:52.650 --> 00:02:56.420
you merge together Hydrogen atoms, and you get Helium and energy

00:02:56.420 --> 00:03:01.760
While on nuclear fission you separate atoms from heavy elements like Uranium or Plutonium,

00:03:01.760 --> 00:03:04.939
which are divided in the nuclear reactors to provide energy.

00:03:04.939 --> 00:03:09.999
So, nuclear fusion can provide us with a lot of energy environmentally safe

00:03:09.999 --> 00:03:14.469
and by "a lot" I mean that 6 liters from water could provide the same energy

00:03:14.469 --> 00:03:19.510
than a ton of coal. So...enough energy to power our Iron man suit.

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:19.769

00:03:19.769 --> 00:03:24.749
Bad news is that for developing a nuclear fusion reactor you need a lot

00:03:24.749 --> 00:03:30.169
of money, so much money that the cost of constructing the first

00:03:30.169 --> 00:03:34.889
fusion reactor is being paid by several countries...and there's also another small detail,

00:03:34.889 --> 00:03:37.489
the reactor is the size of a building.

00:03:37.489 --> 00:03:43.400
In other words, the technology for powering the Iron Man's suit does exist,

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:47.359
but currently it is still being developed. So let's check back in 20 years, shall we?

00:03:47.359 --> 00:03:52.260
But well...so far we have a military exoskeleton in development which could be the armor

